**Smoothing Function Below**
```{r}
#want to change this to remove some of the columns we dont want instead of the many many many columns we DO want now
scrubbed_data <-smooth_data %>% 
  select(stand, release_speed, release_pos_x, release_pos_y, release_pos_z, pfx_x, pfx_z, zone, pitch_type)

scrubbed_data

#CHANGE OUTPUT FILE NAME EACH TIME!!!
write.csv(scrubbed_data, 'Max_Scherzer1.csv')
```


**Remove na for now... will change later to keep the rest of the data and ignore the na in the columns**

```{r}
remove_na <- na.omit(scrubbed_data)


write.csv(remove_na, 'Max_Scherzer_7_22_24.csv')

remove_na
```



